<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pen3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pen,</orth> vb. (partic. <emph>pent;</emph> impf. not found) to confine, to shut up: <cit><quote>he --s her piteous clamours in her head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 681" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 681</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a liquid prisoner --t in walls of glass,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 5, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.133.13" default="NO" valid="yes">133, 13</bibl>. <cit><quote>my --t heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 1, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--t from liberty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.267" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 267</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in his chamber --s himself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 144</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--t to linger but with a grain a day,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 89</bibl></cit>. With <cit><quote>up:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.326" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 326</bibl></cit>.* <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.160" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 3, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 153</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>